From b4c4d709503047a570ccb3bde3c330a7daab4860 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Muna Sinada <muna.sinada@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Sep 2025 11:41:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi:mac80211: fix updating WDS AP_VLAN links

AP_VLAN interface is utilized by both Dynamic VLAN and WDS features.
While they use the same interface type, how they utilize the interface
is different. When it comes to maintaining links, dynamic vlan
maintains the same links as the root AP. For WDS, it maintains the
intersect of root AP links and the links supported by associated STA.

During MLO link reconfiguration, we are observing AP_VLAN interface's
links in a repeater adding a new link that is not supported by
associated STA or not adding a new link the is supported by associated
STA. This is due to ieee80211_update_apvlan_links() not handling WDS
case of intersecting AP's valid links and associated STA valid links.

Add condition for WDS where add parameter is taking AP's update valid
links and associated STA's valid links and storing its intersect. This
will prevent enabling links on AP_VLAN interface the STA does not
support.

Patch-dependency:
subsys/0290-02-UPSTREAM-CP-wifi-mac80211-Add-WDS-changes-to-rework.patch

Patch-work: None

Fixes: Iac38b060ca0 (QSDK:CP: wifi: mac80211: Backport upstream
AP_VLAN interface link handling)

Signed-off-by: Muna Sinada <muna.sinada@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/link.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/net/mac80211/link.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/link.c
@@ -16,12 +16,19 @@ static void ieee80211_update_apvlan_link
 {
 	struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *vlan;
 	struct ieee80211_link_data *link;
+	struct sta_info *sta = NULL;
 
 	list_for_each_entry(vlan, &sdata->u.ap.vlans, u.vlan.list) {
 		unsigned long add = sdata->vif.valid_links;
 		unsigned long rem = ~sdata->vif.valid_links & GENMASK(15,0);
 		int link_id;
 
+		if (vlan->wdev.use_4addr) {
+			sta = rcu_access_pointer(vlan->u.vlan.sta);
+			if (sta)
+				add = add & sta->sta.valid_links;
+		}
+
 		if (add == vlan->vif.valid_links)
 			continue;
 
